1. mutable vs immutable:
    mutable: content of an instance reference can be altered
    immutable: content of an instance reference can not be altered
    String is immutable:
      String text = new String("aabbcc");
      text.replaceAll("aa", "11");
      text will still be aabbcc not 11bbcc
      text = text.replaceAll("aa", "11") - will work
